# xcelium-mcp supervisor watchdog + idle-culler (cron-based, root/admin not required).
#
# See docs/02-design/features/xcelium-mcp-server-process-lifecycle.design.md §7.2.
# Install with: crontab -e   (as the same user xcelium-mcp runs as, e.g. hoseung.lee)
#
# Do not `crontab this-file` blindly if you already have other cron entries —
# merge these lines into your existing crontab instead of overwriting it.
#
# 2026-07-07 cloud0 실측 정정: `/opt/mcp-env/bin/` is root-owned and NOT writable
# by a regular user (confirmed on cloud0), so `pip install -e .` cannot generate
# the xcelium-mcp-supervisor/xcelium-mcp-culler console-script wrappers there.
# Invoke the modules directly via `python3 -m` instead — this works today with
# the existing editable install, no new files needed under /opt/mcp-env/bin/.

@reboot         /usr/bin/flock -n $HOME/.xcelium_mcp/run/supervisor.lock /opt/mcp-env/bin/python3 -m xcelium_mcp.supervisor
* * * * *       /usr/bin/flock -n $HOME/.xcelium_mcp/run/supervisor.lock /opt/mcp-env/bin/python3 -m xcelium_mcp.supervisor
*/5 * * * *     /opt/mcp-env/bin/python3 -m xcelium_mcp.idle_culler
